  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Burkina Faso Acute Crisis Joint Response</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">According to a WV needs assessment (13-17 Dec. 2021), in the Centre-Nord 73% of the households in Kaya, Boala, Pissila, Tougouri and Koungoussi are IDPs. In the Sahel region in Dori, Sebba, Djibo, Gorom Gorom, 81% are IDPs. In the Sahel, Nord, and Boucle du Mouhoun, out of 797 households covered, 623 have no water to wash their hands or to drink safely. In the Sahel, out of 552 households covered, 354 households often do not have enough to eat, while 361 feel exposed to protection risks. The response targets 12.551 people from these households.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Burkina Faso is in the grip of a triple crisis of armed conflict, climate change, and COVID-19. Poor infrastructure and services have exacerbated IDPs and host communities&#x2019; needs of food, WASH and protection support, with the overall severity of needs being greatest in the Centre-Nord and the Sahel region. The response consists of WASH, Protection, and MPC interventions in Dori (Sahel), Kaya, and Koungoussi (Centre Nord) to address the urgent needs of the most vulnerable IDPs and the host community.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To meet the needs of the most vulnerable IDPs and host communities in the North of Burkina Faso through interventions in WASH, Protection and MPC.</narrative>
  </description>
